news.title: Preclinical research shows that COVID-19 infection may dysregulate NAD+ synthesis
news.summary: A new preclinical study found that SARS-CoV-2 (the virus that causes COVID-19) infection of cell lines, infected ferrets, and a deceased patient’s lung dysregulates nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide (NAD+) synthesis and utilization.
